The Police dragon patrol team during a routine stop and search duty along Warri/Sapele road arrested a 33-year-old suspect, Akpoyerinebele with a stolen vehicle while his accomplice escaped from the scene of the incident. It was learnt that the Police intercepted a Toyota Venza with Reg. no. FKJ 420 GT, chassis number 4t3bk3bb0bu056957 and Engine number 6668351 in Grey colour, driven by the suspect in the company of another occupant (name unknown). The other occupant reportedly took to his heels and ran into the bush just as the driver was arrested by the Police. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer DSP Bright Edafe. He said, “Upon searching of the vehicle, a phone number was found inside. During the course of the investigation, the owner of the vehicle was contacted through the phone number found in the vehicle. “The owner of the vehicle confirmed that the vehicle was snatched at NDC road Ozoro at gunpoint by a five-man robbery gang at about 0100hrs of the same date. “Manhunt for the other fleeing suspect is ongoing.”